replies.bodyText:
looks like the CloseHandler owns the responsibility of calling shutdownOutput() and the associated state machine around it. for H2 this will currently close the channel more abruptly with close() which may mean the local peer won't finish sending currently buffered/pending data. despite the spec saying close down the connection immediately, discarding any pending writes.we can make a best effort to flush our queues without losing much...
         @Override
         void closeChannelOutbound(final Channel channel) {
-            channel.close();
+            channel.writeAndFlush(EmptyBuffer.EMPTY_BUFFER).addListener(ChannelFutureListener.CLOSE);
         }
we may want to inject a similar event at the ServiceTalk layer to catch any inflight signals (which maybe offloaded). however we wouldn't want lack of demand (or cancellation) to prevent the cleanup process (so maybe not worth the trouble). it would be good to test this at the protocol layer as I recall similar misses in Netty.

